                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        <customfield id="customfield_12310183" key="com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.customfieldtypes:textarea">
                        <customfieldname>Steps to Reproduce</customfieldname>
                        <customfieldvalues>
                            <customfieldvalue>&lt;p&gt;Configure Failover deployments with JBDC as per:&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-US/Red_Hat_JBoss_Fuse/6.1/html-single/Configuring_and_Running_Red_Hat_JBoss_Fuse/#ESBRuntimeFailover&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-US/Red_Hat_JBoss_Fuse/6.1/html-single/Configuring_and_Running_Red_Hat_JBoss_Fuse/#ESBRuntimeFailover&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Start the master instance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Start the slave instance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Try to stop the slave instance. We would see it fails with error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason is that we see the port file which is used to stop the instance is not created on the slave instance in the scenario of failover deployments.&lt;/p&gt;</customfieldvalue>

